    <h1>About The Cosmic Variety Show</h1>
    <p>Three polymaths. One channel. The universe explained, questioned, and redesigned.</p>
    <p><strong>Buckminster Fuller</strong> sees the whole system — the planet as a spaceship, humanity as crew, design as the lever.</p>
    <p><strong>Richard Feynman</strong> takes it apart — with joy, with rigor, with a joke that turns out to be the deepest truth in the room.</p>
    <p><strong>Carl Sagan</strong> shows us where we are — a pale blue dot, suspended in a sunbeam, and the most important thing any of us will ever see.</p>
    <p>They never met in the same room. But their ideas meet here.</p>
</article>
